      • getCurveValues

        public double[] getCurveValues()
        Retrieve the values which define the curve. The method returns an array of 21 doubles, each representing 5% of the duration. This includes an entry for 0%. The total of the values in the array must be 100%. Note that the CONTOURED enum will return null as the values for the work or cost per time period have been handcrafted and do not use a curve.
        Returns:
        curve values
